          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1602249149551-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crack your <strong>egg[s] </strong>into a bowl with the <strong>remaining ground smoked paprika </strong>and beat with a fork</p><p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a plate</p><p>Coat your<strong> chicken breast portion[s]</strong> in the <strong>beaten egg</strong>, then press firmly into the <strong>panko</strong> <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> until evenly coated – this is your <strong>breaded chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1602249777053-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1602249777053-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1602249777053-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1602249777053-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1602249777053-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>breaded chicken</strong> to a separate <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>(this will stop them sticking!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in 2 batches!</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until the chicken is golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>crispy breaded chicken</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2731---step-5-copy-2-1607526328384-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2731---step-5-copy-2-1607526328384-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2731---step-5-copy-2-1607526328384-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2731---step-5-copy-2-1607526328384-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2731---step-5-copy-2-1607526328384-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has caramelised, add your <strong>cider vinegar</strong>,<strong> honey </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>water </strong>to the pan</p><p>Increase the heat to medium and cook for a further 5 min or until a sticky sauce has formed – this is your<strong> bacon jam</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch the jam like a hawk to make sure it doesn't burn!</p><p>Cut your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half, then add<strong> </strong>to a baking tray (cut-side up) and put the tray in the oven for 4-5 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1602249192736-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1602249192736-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1602249192736-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1602249192736-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1602249192736-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>sweetcorn cobette[s] </strong>to a pot and cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-7 min or until they’re tender and have turned bright yellow</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cobette[s]</strong>, return them to the pot and add a knob of <strong>butter </strong>– these are your<strong> buttery sweetcorn cobette</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1602249233020-x200.jpg",
